## **1.2. Database Design** {#1.2.-database-design}

*Figure 2\. Database diagram*

***Table Description***

| \# | Table | Description |
| ----- | ----- | ----- |
| **1** | users | Stores user accounts (students, instructors, admins): user\_id, username, password hash, role, contact info (phone\_number, email) |
| **2** | students | Stores only student accounts: student\_id (derived from “users” table through “user\_id”)  |
| **3** | lecturers | Stores only lecturer accounts: lecturer\_id (derived from “users” table through “user\_id”)  |
| **4** | admins | Stores only admin accounts: admin\_id (derived from “users” table through “user\_id”)  |
| **5** | semesters | Lists academic terms by code and year (e.g. Spring, Fall) |
| **6** | degree\_list | Lists degrees of student/lecturer, including the graduation date and GPA |
| **7** | courses | Catalog of courses: course code, name, credit, hours and type (Lecture/Lab) |
| **8** | classes | Course offerings per term: classID, linked course, semester, capacity, current enrollment |
| **9** | schedules | Class schedules; room assignment and time slot  |
| **10** | enrollments | Records students registration in classes: enrollment date, grade, status  |
| **11** | class\_instructors  | Assigns instructors to classes and their role (primary and secondary), linked with “lecturer” table through “instructor\_id”, derived from “lecturer\_id” |
| **12** | announcements | Class announcements posted by instructors: title, content, timestamp  |
| **13** | materials  | Learning materials for classes: file title, description, path, uploader, upload timestamp  |
| **14** | assignments | Class assignments: title, description, due date, maximum score |
| **15** | submissions | Student submissions of assignments: submission timestamp, content/file path, score |
| **16** | attendance\_records | Attendance tracking per class session: date, status (present/absent/late/excused), recorder  |
| **17** | tuition\_payments | Tuition payment records by student and term: payment date, method, payment status  |

# **2\. Code Designs** {#2.-code-designs}

## **2.1. Account Access & Management** {#2.1.-account-access-&-management}

### **2.1.1. User login** {#2.1.1.-user-login}

This function allow users to log into the system using their given account and password

#### **2.1.1.1. Class Diagram**

![][image1]

*Figure 3\. Class diagram of **Authentication***

#### **2.1.1.2. Class Specifications**

*Login Class*

| \# | Table | Description |
| ----- | ----- | ----- |
| **1** | username: string | Stores username input by the user |
| **2** | password: string | Stores password input by the user |
| **3** | login() : boolean | Validates the credentials and returns true if the user is authenticated. |

*User Class*

| \# | Table | Description |
| ----- | ----- | ----- |
| **1** | user\_id: string | Unique identifier for the user. |
| **2** | username: string | The username of the user |
| **3** | full name: string | The full name of the user |
| **4** | role: string | User’s role (student/lecturer/admin) |
| **5** | DoB: date | User’s Date of Birth |
| **6** | phone number: string | The phone number of the user |
| **7** | email: string | User’s email |
| **8** | password: string | User’s password |
| **9** | logout(): void | Logs the user out |
| **10** | VierUserAccount(): User | Displays user account details. |
| **11** | resetPassword(): void | Resets the password of the user. |

*Admin Class*

| \# | Table | Description |
| ----- | ----- | ----- |
| **1** | ViewOtherUserAccount() : User | Allows admin to view details of other user accounts. |
| **2** | AddAccount() : void | Adds a new user account to the system. |
| **3** | DeleteAccount() : void | Removes a user account from the system. |

*Database Class*

| \# | Table | Description |
| ----- | ----- | ----- |
| **1** | \[property placeholder\] | Represents data storage and connection methods. |
| **2** | \[method placeholder\] | Handles validation of user credentials. |

*Accounts Class*

| \# | Table | Description |
| ----- | ----- | ----- |
| **1** | \[property placeholder\] | Represents account data and related operations. |

*Student/Lecturer Class*

| \# | Table | Description |
| ----- | ----- | ----- |
| **1** | \[property placeholder\] | Represents the student or lecturer details. |
